{"word":"κοινωνός","slug":"κοινωνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κοινωνός</b></el> <el>(κοινωνός, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κοινός'><el>κοινός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a companion, partner</i>, <el>τινος</el> <i>in</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ὁ τοῦ κακοῦ κ.</el> <i>accomplice in</i> the evil, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; also, <el>τινι</el> in a thing, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>a partner, fellow</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> = <a href='S:κοινός'><el>κοινός</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}